Complete Flow of Your App

When the app launches:

                    Recipe_ManagerApp.swift
                            │
                            ▼
                    SplashScreen.swift
                            │
                            ▼
                    HomeView.swift
                            │
                            ▼
                    RecipeManager.swift
                            │
                            ▼
                    Recipe.swift
                    

1. Recipe_ManagerApp.swift : This is the entry point of the application. Without this file, the app cannot start.
        Connected With -
            Recipe_ManagerApp

                ↓

            SplashScreen

Only one connection.

2. SplashScreen.swift : It exists only for a few seconds.Shows Logo, Animation, Loading, Navigate to HomeView.

3. HomeView.swift : This is the heart of the UI. Almost everything starts here.It communicates with RecipeManager using @StateObject  because HomeView owns the data. Responsibilities:

                    ✅ Display all recipes

                    ✅ Search recipes

                    ✅ Delete recipes

                    ✅ Navigate to details

                    ✅ Open Add Recipe screen

Diagram

HomeView

│

├── RecipeCardView

├── AddRecipeView

└── RecipeDetailView

This is your main screen.


4. RecipeCardView.swift : Think of this as a reusable card. Instead of writing- Image, Title, Category, Time, Heart, inside HomeView again and again, we created  RecipeCardView So HomeView does :
                                    RecipeCardView(recipe: recipe) 100 times.
                                    

//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------//

Project follows CRUD Operations :

CRUD Operation   --    Where it Happens
Create  --              AddRecipeView → RecipeManager.addRecipe() adds a new recipe.
Read    --              HomeView displays all recipes and RecipeDetailView displays a selected recipe.
Update  --              toggleFavorite() in RecipeManager updates the isFavorite property of a recipe.
Delete  --              Swipe-to-delete in HomeView calls deleteRecipe() in RecipeManager.


